				</position>
			</language>
			<language ident="LA">
				<position book_orientation="0" place="tail">
					<marginalia_text>
						Seneca, duo, [[*6[r]]: Tranquillitas, et Constantia: Lipsius, tria, Tranq[uillitas], Const[antia], et Pietas.]
							<!-- Continues onto facing page, tail, Ha2.077r -->
					</marginalia_text>
					<person name="Seneca"/>
				</position>
			</language>
			<translation>
				Anyone's mind can be anything. The intellect is all things.
				There are the two words of Epictetus: be patient and desist.
				Seneca, in two. [[*6[r]]: Tranquillity and Constancy. Lipsius, in three words: Tranquillity, Constancy, and Piety.]
			</translation>
		</marginalia>
		
		<marginalia hand="Italian">
			<language ident="LA">
				<position book_orientation="90" place="left_margin">
					<marginalia_text>
						Viri est, quotidiana arte, et exercitatione efficere, vt sua singula membra plus
						valeant aliorum membris: et sui externi, interniq[ue] sensus alioru[m] sensibus
						pra[e]polleant. vt 
					</marginalia_text>
					<emphasis method="pen" text="sua singula membra" type="straight"/>
					<emphasis method="pen" text="Sui externi, interniq[ue] sensus " type="straight"/>
				</position>
				<position book_orientation="90" place="right_margin">
					<marginalia_text>
						vt validissimarum partium inductione, ipsum Totum fiat
						Longè validissimum. nobilissima mundi diligentia.
					</marginalia_text>
					<emphasis method="pen" text="partium inductione" type="straight"/>
					<emphasis method="pen" text="Totum fiat" type="straight"/>
				</position>
			</language>
			<translation>
				Man's task, through daily art and exercise, is to bring to pass that his individual members are worth more
				than those of other men, and that his external and internal senses are much stronger than those of other men;
				in order that, with the creation of most powerful parts, his entire person becomes by far the strongest. 
				His diligence the most noble of the world.
			</translation>
		</marginalia>
		
